Responsibilities

Perform troubleshooting and provide day-to-day support including hardware, software, end-user and helpdesk;
Perform hardware installation, configuration or maintenance, including PC, notebook, Mac, server, printer and other computer peripheral devices;
Conduct software installation, configuration or maintenance including MS-Office, Outlook, Windows, Mac, Adobe products, AntiVirus and other office applications;
Provide regular testing of IT equipment and monitoring of IT equipment status and ah hoc on site support;

Requirements

IVE/Diploma holder in Information System, Computer Science, Computer Engineering or related disciplines;
1 year experience in IT technical / deskside support will be an advantage, fresh graduates are also welcomed;
Knowledge in Windows;
Knowledge in AD, DNS, FTP, TCP/IP, POP3, SMTP & SNMP;
Good computer knowledge of MS-Word, Excel, PowerPoint;
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese
Immediately available will be an advantage

We offer excellent career development opportunities to unleash your potential, competitive remuneration package including a 5-day work week, medical insurance & dental plan, discretionary bonus, staff training and staff purchasing discount etc.


Interest parties, please simply click "Apply now" to submit your application with full resume stating current & expected salary and the availability for reporting duty. 

You are welcome to visit our website to know more about us: www.popular.com.hk or http://ephhk.popularworldhk.com.


Personal data provided by job applicants will be kept strictly confidential and will be used solely for employment related purpose.  Only short-listed candidates will be contacted.

Job Responsibilities

Responsible for IT helpdesk work, quickly responding and dealing with user desktop problems and needs;
Responsible for the daily maintenance of IT desktops and related equipment, including PCs, printers, scanners, electronic scales, and other equipment and related software maintenance;
Responsible for the installation and distribution of IT desktop related equipment and systems;
Responsible for the security and stability of the IT network (including wireless network) environment;
Responsible for the management and maintenance of CCTV monitoring equipment;
Assist the asset department in managing and updating assets. Including asset warehousing, issuance, inventory, maintenance, and scrap management.

Requirements

Computer-related major, with practical related work experience;
Possess strong problem analysis and solving skills, high sense of responsibility, good professional ethics, a strong sense of service, and proactive;
Proficient in Windows, macOS, and other operating systems, proficient in the installation and troubleshooting of office software and common software;
Skilled in solving the faults of terminal equipment such as PCs, printers, telephones, scanners, electronic scales, etc.;
Master the configuration, use, and policy formulation of mainstream VPN, online behavior management, access, firewall, and other security equipment;
Master the configuration, maintenance, fault diagnosis, and optimization of routers, switches, WLCs, APs, and other network equipment;
Master the basic use and maintenance of CCTV monitoring equipment;
Understand enterprise IT infrastructure, and have a certain understanding of weak current integrated wiring, servers, virtualization, etc.

Interested Parties please feel free to click the button above for APPLYING/ WhatsApp / call 6603 4144

崗位職責

負責IThelpdesk工作，快速相應和處理用戶桌面端問題和需求；
負責IT桌面及相關設備的日常維護工作，包括PC、打印機、掃描儀、電子秤等設備及相關軟件維護；
負責IT桌面相關設備和系統的安裝、配發工作；
負責IT網絡（包含無線網絡）環境安全穩定；
負責CCTV監控設備管理、維護工作；
協助資產部門進行資產的管理與更新。包括資產入庫、發放、盤點、維修、報廢管理。

入職要求

計算機相關專業，具有實際相關工作經驗；
具備較強的問題分析和解決能力，高度責任感，良好的職業道德，服務意識強，積極進取；
熟練掌握Windows、MacOS等操作系統相關知識，熟練office辦公軟件及常用軟件的安裝和故障解決；
熟練解決PC機、打印機、電話、掃描儀、電子秤等終端設備的故障；
掌握主流VPN、上網行為管理、准入、防火牆等安全設備的配置、使用及策略的製定；
掌握路由器、交換機、WLC、AP等網絡設備的配置、維護、故障診斷及優化；
掌握CCTV監控設備的基本使用和維護；
了解企業IT基礎架構，對弱電綜合佈線、服務器、虛擬化等方面有一定認識。

有意者請隨時點擊上方按鈕申請/whatsapp/致電6603 4144

DEAR TALENT, YOUR MOVE!

Being the new rising airline since 2013, we are the Hong Kong’s only Low Cost Carrier (LCC) offering you safe and flexible service options to Hong Kong and beyond.

We’re on a mission to inspire you to be different, to shake things up, to inspire the spirit of adventure by bringing you to fascinating destinations that few others serve.

Spread your wings and fly with us!

What will you do? 

Lead a small team to maintain daily IT Infrastructure operation to support internal users within SLA under ITIL standard;
Support Security team to handle security events in IT infrastructure environment;
Support internal audit to assess different IT areas;
Develop and maintain formal guidelines, policies, and procedures to ensure the smooth operation;
Manage external vendor to provide technical support on corporate IT Infrastructure with emphasis on the internal network, servers, Microsoft office365 environment and cloud infrastructure;
Manage external vendor to provide technical support on Airport IT Infrastructure with emphasis on Express IP, AviNet, ACARS and EDI about Cargo / Crew / Passenger Information Filing;
Plan, setup, lead and manage the IT Infrastructure and End-user Technology Strategy including disaster recovery planning;
Research on new technology, identify technology gaps, develop and deploy Infrastructure solutions;
Remediate Risk & Vulnerability for Infrastructure and End-user computing;
Drive the continuous improvement to all IT Infrastructure related services;
Determine how to leverage enabling technologies to implement innovative IT infrastructure solutions to support the business
Coach and mentor team members;
Travel occasionally for new station setup/support; 
Support ad-hoc duties as assigned.

We are a perfect match, if you are:

University graduate in Computer Technology or related discipline;
Minimum 6 years of related working experiences in IT security with 2 years of supervisor post;
Strong technical knowledge in all aspects of IT Infrastructure especially in Microsoft Office365, Fortinet, Azure/Alibaba cloud and End-user computing;
Sound Knowledgeable on SOC, DLP and SIEM;
Certification on networking (such as CCNA, CCNP, CCIE);
ITILv3 Foundation Certification is a must;
Basic knowledge of common information security management frameworks, such as ISO 27001, CobiT, ITIL, PCI DSS.

Your Future Work Life?

Work flexibly with staggered working hours and flexible workplace
Dress Casual and Smart everyday
Work in a newly-designed office with open seating, stylish breakout areas, game room, gym and free coffee…
Work with a group of energetic and multicultural professionals (up to 50 nationalities!)
Have great fun in Snack Friday, New Year Market, Fly with your Kids Day, Basketball Team…
Have your voice heard through Townhalls, Crew forums, CEO live sessions etc.

What will you enjoy?

Fly anywhere we fly for free plus taxes during leisure with your friends and family
Special privileges to buy duty free products
